;a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:571:\"<p>OK WordPress was updating itself, themes or plugins and something went wrong and now your WordPress site is stuck in Maintenance Mode with a message on the screen that reads &#8220;“Briefly unavailable for scheduled maintenance. Check back in a minute.” and you can not get into your wp-admin or view your site. Learn how to [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wordpress-stuck-in-maintenance-mode/\">WordPress stuck in Maintenance Mode</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.seedprod.com\">SeedProd</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"John Turner\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:2999:\"<p>OK WordPress was updating itself, themes or plugins and something went wrong and now your WordPress site is stuck in Maintenance Mode with a message on the screen that reads &#8220;“<em>Briefly unavailable for scheduled maintenance. Check back in a minute.</em>” and you can not get into your wp-admin or view your site.</p>\n<p>Learn how to get out of Maintenance Mode when WordPress gets stuck. Follow these steps to quickly solve the issue.</p>\n<ol>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.seedprod.com/how-to-ftp-into-wordpress/\">FTP into your WordPress site</a> and look for a file called <strong>.maintenance</strong> in the WordPress root. (If you do not see this file make sure to adjust your setting in your ftp client and make hidden files visible.</li>\n<li>Delete this file.</li>\n</ol>\n<div id=\"attachment_2369\" style=\"width: 410px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/delete-maintenance-file-wordpress-1.jpg\"><img data-attachment-id=\"2369\" data-permalink=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wordpress-stuck-in-maintenance-mode/delete-maintenance-file-wordpress-2/\" data-orig-file=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/delete-maintenance-file-wordpress-1.jpg\" data-orig-size=\"539,508\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"delete-maintenance-file-wordpress\" data-image-description=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/delete-maintenance-file-wordpress-1-400x377.jpg\" data-large-file=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/delete-maintenance-file-wordpress-1.jpg\" class=\"wp-image-2369 size-medium\" src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/delete-maintenance-file-wordpress-1-400x377.jpg\" width=\"400\" height=\"377\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/delete-maintenance-file-wordpress-1-400x377.jpg 400w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/delete-maintenance-file-wordpress-1.jpg 539w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">How to get WordPress out of Maintenance Mode</p></div>\n<p>That&#8217;s it! WordPress should now be back to normal and serving your regular site.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.seedprod.com/how-to-create-custom-maintenance-mode-page-wordpress/\">Learn How to Customize the WordPress Maintenance Message</a></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wordpress-stuck-in-maintenance-mode/\">WordPress stuck in Maintenance Mode</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.seedprod.com\">SeedProd</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:66:\"https://www.seedprod.com/wordpress-stuck-in-maintenance-mode/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:30:\"com-wordpress:feed-additions:1\";a:1:{s:7:\"post-id\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"2361\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:42:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:6:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:71:\"How to Create a Custom Maintenance Page in WordPress with Free Template\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:78:\"https://www.seedprod.com/how-to-create-custom-maintenance-mode-page-wordpress/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:86:\"https://www.seedprod.com/how-to-create-custom-maintenance-mode-page-wordpress/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 25 Oct 2016 15:26:50 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"How To\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:32:\"https://www.seedprod.com/?p=2344\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:664:\"<p>WordPress has it&#8217;s own Maintenance Mode it goes into when it performs a core, themes or plugins updates. The picture above shows what you see when WordPress is performing these updates. What most people don&#8217;t know is that this is different from what a WordPress Maintenance Mode plugins would do. Learn more about the difference between WordPress&#8217;s [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.seedprod.com/how-to-create-custom-maintenance-mode-page-wordpress/\">How to Create a Custom Maintenance Page in WordPress with Free Template</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.seedprod.com\">SeedProd</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"John Turner\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10192:\"<div id=\"attachment_2346\" style=\"width: 410px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/wordpress-maintenance-mode.jpg\"><img data-attachment-id=\"2346\" data-permalink=\"https://www.seedprod.com/how-to-create-custom-maintenance-mode-page-wordpress/wordpress-maintenance-mode-3/\" data-orig-file=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/wordpress-maintenance-mode.jpg\" data-orig-size=\"718,581\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"wordpress-maintenance-mode\" data-image-description=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/wordpress-maintenance-mode-400x324.jpg\" data-large-file=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/wordpress-maintenance-mode.jpg\" class=\"wp-image-2346 size-medium\" src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/wordpress-maintenance-mode-400x324.jpg\" alt=\"wordpress-maintenance-mode\" width=\"400\" height=\"324\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/wordpress-maintenance-mode-400x324.jpg 400w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/wordpress-maintenance-mode.jpg 718w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Default WordPress Maintenance Page</p></div>\n<p>WordPress has it&#8217;s own Maintenance Mode it goes into when it performs a core, themes or plugins updates. The picture above shows what you see when WordPress is performing these updates. What most people don&#8217;t know is that this is different from what a WordPress <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/coming-soon/\">Maintenance Mode plugins</a> would do. Learn more about the difference <a href=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wordpress-maintenance-mode/\">between WordPress&#8217;s built in maintenance mode vs what a maintenance mode plugin</a> does. In a nutshell a maintenance plugin will hide your site while you make changes, you still have access to the frontend and wp-admin backend, while the WordPress built in maintenance mode hides the entire site while the software itself is updating, no access to the frontend or backend. Therefore maintenance mode plugins won&#8217;t work when WordPress is doing it&#8217;s built in maintenance process. Today I&#8217;m going to show you how to customize the default maintenance message page which says &#8220;<em>Briefly unavailable for scheduled maintenance. Check back in a minute.</em>&#8221; to a custom html page and even how to collect emails on this page while your site is down.</p>\n<h2>How to Create a Custom WordPress Maintenance Mode Page</h2>\n<p>To create a custom maintenance message for WordPress you simply need to create a file called <strong>maintenance.php</strong> and upload this file to the root of your <strong>wp-content</strong> folder. (<a href=\"https://www.seedprod.com/how-to-ftp-into-wordpress/\">Learn how to ftp into WordPress</a>) This page will now be used when WordPress is performing updates to your site.</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_2349\" style=\"width: 780px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/how-to-custom-wordpress-maintenence-page.jpg\"><img data-attachment-id=\"2349\" data-permalink=\"https://www.seedprod.com/how-to-create-custom-maintenance-mode-page-wordpress/how-to-custom-wordpress-maintenence-page/\" data-orig-file=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/how-to-custom-wordpress-maintenence-page.jpg\" data-orig-size=\"770,436\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"how-to-custom-wordpress-maintenence-page\" data-image-description=\"&lt;p&gt;how-to-custom-wordpress-maintenence-page&lt;/p&gt;\n\" data-medium-file=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/how-to-custom-wordpress-maintenence-page-400x226.jpg\" data-large-file=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/how-to-custom-wordpress-maintenence-page.jpg\" class=\"size-full wp-image-2349\" src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/how-to-custom-wordpress-maintenence-page.jpg\" alt=\"Upload a file called maitenance.php to your wp-content folder.\" width=\"770\" height=\"436\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/how-to-custom-wordpress-maintenence-page.jpg 770w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/how-to-custom-wordpress-maintenence-page-400x226.jpg 400w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/how-to-custom-wordpress-maintenence-page-768x435.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 770px) 100vw, 770px\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Upload a file called maintenance.php to your wp-content folder.</p></div>\n<p>One thing to note is you&#8217;ll want to make sure you put the correct http status code on this page so search engines know your site is in maintenance mode and will not index your maintenance page. This would be very bad for your SEO. To do this put this line of code on top of your <strong>maintenance.php</strong> file.<br />\n<code><br />\n&lt;?php<br />\nheader(\'HTTP/1.1 503 Service Temporarily Unavailable\');<br />\nheader(\'Status: 503 Service Temporarily Unavailable\');<br />\nheader(\'Retry-After: 600\');<br />\n?&gt;<br />\n</code></p>\n<p>This tells search engines that your site is in unavailable and to try back in 10 minutes. WordPress core, themes and plugins updates usually only take a few seconds to update but we&#8217;ll put 10 minutes to be on the safe side. Below that http status code you can now add a custom message or html to create a better looking maintenance page or even add code to collect emails while your site is down.</p>\n<h2>Free Customizable WordPress Maintenance Mode Page Template</h2>\n<p>If you don&#8217;t know html we have included a download to our free maintenance mode template.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/custom-wordpress-maintenance-mode.jpg\"><img data-attachment-id=\"2354\" data-permalink=\"https://www.seedprod.com/how-to-create-custom-maintenance-mode-page-wordpress/custom-wordpress-maintenance-mode/\" data-orig-file=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/custom-wordpress-maintenance-mode.jpg\" data-orig-size=\"916,737\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"custom-wordpress-maintenance-mode\" data-image-description=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/custom-wordpress-maintenance-mode-400x322.jpg\" data-large-file=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/custom-wordpress-maintenance-mode-800x644.jpg\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-2354\" src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/custom-wordpress-maintenance-mode.jpg\" alt=\"custom wordpress maintenance mode page\" width=\"916\" height=\"737\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/custom-wordpress-maintenance-mode.jpg 916w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/custom-wordpress-maintenance-mode-400x322.jpg 400w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/custom-wordpress-maintenance-mode-768x618.jpg 768w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/